I started DXTalent because friends at IIITDM kept asking for a structured way to learn digital
transformation skills without drowning in enterprise jargon. Here are a few lessons from sprinting the
first version into the world:

1. **Scope your AI surface area.** Gemini was great at drafting lesson blueprints, but only after I fed it
   real DX maturity data and a templatized voice. Guardrails > magic.
2. **Gamification must feel earned.** Six leagues and twenty badges sound fun until you try to prevent
   cheating. I added server-side validation and human spot checks before unlocking anything.
3. **Charge early.** Integrating Stripe from day one forced me to define what "value" meant for learners vs
   recruiters. That clarity shaped the roadmap more than any OKR doc.

